Ad Text:
What if your ML work didn’t just run in a notebook, but powered autonomous systems to make split-second decisions when GPS fails, comms drop, and backup isn’t coming?We’re building autonomous aerial systems designed for contested, multi-domain environments — systems that need to perceive, decide, and act in the real world.

This isn’t a research role. It’s about deploying, scaling, and improving ML models that directly shape mission outcomes.

The Role
You’ll bridge the gap between ML research and real-world deployment — taking reinforcement learning and related methods from paper to production.

Build and maintain data pipelines that keep training datasets clean, reliable, and scalable.
Deploy, monitor, and continuously improve models in production — balancing accuracy, performance, and cost.
Design experimentation and evaluation frameworks that combine quantitative metrics, expert feedback, and field results.
Prototype, test, and refine new architectures or approaches, translating them into robust systems.
Collaborate across product, systems, and autonomy engineers to integrate ML into operational platforms.
Stay informed on the latest research — but focus on what actually works in deployment.
You’ll be hands-on with reinforcement learning, but success here comes from strong engineering judgement and end-to-end delivery capability — not publishing papers.

Who This Might Suit
You hold a PhD or equivalent background in ML, robotics, computer science, or a related field.
You’ve also gained industry experience building, deploying, and maintaining ML systems in production.
You’re comfortable working from idea to implementation: data prep, training, evaluation, deployment, and iteration.
Understands Reinforcement Learning concepts and can translate it into deployable models. 
You should be confident with:

Training and debugging ML models.
Building reproducible experimentation pipelines.
Using modern MLOps tools for deployment and monitoring.
Turning research insights into functional code and scalable systems.
Caring about how your models perform outside of simulation.
Why Apply?
Full-time, permanent role 
Real systems, not just simulation.
High-agency, low-politics environment.
Pathways to grow into technical leadership or deep IC.
A team that values capability, impact, and pragmatism over credentials.
Interested?
You don’t need a polished CV to start the conversation - just reach out to thais@theonset.com.au and we’ll take it from there.

Working for Signify means being creative and adaptive while working in a fast-paced company. Our culture of continuous learning and commitment to diversity and inclusion creates an environment that allows you to build your skills and career while transforming our industry.

As the world leader in lighting, we’re constantly ahead of the curve. Through our leadership in connected lighting and the Internet of Things, we’re breaking new grounds in data analytics, AI, and smart homes, offices, cities and more!

Signify is one of the few companies in the world to achieve carbon neutrality and our next sustainability goals are even bolder: doubling our positive impact on the environment and society by 2025.

We’re on the lookout for a talented Firmware (Embedded Software) Development Engineer to join our Sydney Dynalite R&D Team, a part of our global Signify Intelligent Building R&D Team, which specializes in creating leading-edge Connected Building & Lighting Control solutions for residential, office, retail, hospitality, industry, sport and public indoor and outdoor space applications world-wide…




What you’ll do

As a part of our Global Systems Engineering Team located in Moorebank, Sydney, in your day-to-day work you will be responsible for:

Developing, testing and releasing embedded code for our innovative Connected IoT Lighting propositions and products, which are manufactured and deployed locally and globally on many iconic projects and landmark buildings.

Brainstorming with the Team of passionate professionals locally and globally our next breakthrough innovation in Connected IoT Lighting, turning customer needs into solutions and shaping the Design and Architecture of our Systems, to bring Human-Centric Lighting Solutions and Value Beyond Illumination to our Customers and Business Partners.




What you’ll need

We are looking for a recent Engineering Graduate in Computer Science, Software or Electronics Engineering, with the ability to work in a global SAFe Agile team.

Skills and knowledge requirements:

Hands-on “C” programming of ARM-based Embedded Systems with sound debugging and problem-solving skills and ability to contribute to “peer reviews”

Good understanding of Embedded HW and interfaces. HW design experience would be an advantage.

Hands-on experience with JTAG, Oscilloscope & Logic Analysers. Experience with Wireshark (or similar Network protocol analysers) would be an advantage

Experience with Linux and RTOS (or other Open Source Software) would be an advantage

Experience with Static Code analysis tools (e.g. SonarQube, Coverity) and CI-CD environment following Coding standards & best industry practices would be an advantage

Experience in SAFe Agile WoW would be an advantage

Understanding of Data Collection (sensing) and Digital Signal Processing on Embedded platforms would be an advantage




What you’ll get in return

Flexible working arrangements

Competitive salary package based on experience

Extensive set of tools to drive your career, such as a personalised learning platform, free training and coaching

Opportunity to buy Signify/Philips products with discount




We’re offering multiple opportunities for career development, like mentoring, coaching and stretch assignments, with strong international exposure for dynamic profiles. Learning is fundamental to our culture. Through continuous learning, we are transforming the industry. You have the chance to learn every day, acquire new skills and perspectives through customized online programs, and on-the-job experiences.

Founding/Lead Robotics Engineer Sydney | Full-time | Hybrid | Up to $200k + super

The Mission
A small team in Sydney is teaching humanoid robots to use their hands. Not in simulation or the cloud, but on the robot itself.
They’ve built a lightweight, adaptive intelligence that learns to move, grasp, and act in unfamiliar environments without heavy datasets or retraining.
Now they need a senior engineer to take that brain and make it move.

What You’ll Do


Build and refine manipulation and control pipelines on Jetson hardware


Develop perception and SLAM modules within ROS2


Optimise inference performance, latency, and stability for real-time operation


Coordinate sensor fusion across cameras, force sensors, and depth inputs


Work closely with AI researchers to close the loop between model and movement


Deploy and test robotic systems in both simulated and live environments


What You Bring


Strong programming skills in C++ and Python


Deep familiarity with ROS / ROS2


Proven experience across SLAM, perception, and control architectures


Hands-on experience deploying on embedded platforms (Jetson, Orin)


Understanding of multi-modal AI or vision–action pipelines


Curiosity, precision, and the ability to turn theory into motion


Why It Matters


The system’s intelligence is inspired by insect cognition – lightweight, adaptive, and efficient


Runs locally, consumes minimal compute, and learns general behaviours instead of fixed tasks


Enables large-scale deployment in industries facing critical labour shortages


The Opportunity


Join a small, senior engineering group taking robotics from R&D to commercial rollout


Work directly with founders who have moved from research to real-world deployment


Leadership potential and huge growth opportunities as the company grows


Backed by international investors with major expansion planned


How to Apply
If you want to build robots that think and act, and see your work move from lab to production; reach out.

Contact
Toby Tank
toby@theonset.com.au
0468 524 271

Optus is an Australian telecommunications company, delivering more than 11 million services to our customers every day across mobile, broadband and digital solutions.



Join our newly formed AI Engineering tribe and play a pivotal role in shaping the future of AI-powered integration platforms. As a Senior Software Engineer, you'll lead the evolution of our integration architecture—designing secure, scalable APIs that connect core services with cutting-edge AI capabilities. You'll influence architectural direction, technology choices (including Gen AI, vector databases, and frameworks like SpringAI, LangChain, CrewAI), and API standards that underpin our customer experiences. This is a unique opportunity to make a direct impact on how we build and scale AI-enabled services across our ecosystem.



What you'll do

Design and implement scalable, secure APIs that integrate with AI services and LLMs (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
Lead development using Spring Boot 3.x, WebFlux, and Apigee, driving best practices in performance and security
Collaborate with AI engineers to build endpoints for model inferencing, vector search, and agentic workflows
Apply secure API patterns (OAuth2, JWT) to protect sensitive data and support AI model operations
Drive observability and reliability across services, ensuring smooth and resilient user experiences
Translate business goals into technical designs in partnership with Product Owners and stakeholders
Lead architecture reviews and foster knowledge sharing around AI integration and tools like GitHub Copilot
Align with Platform Engineering and MLOps to enable automated deployment of AI-enabled services

Core Skills

Deep expertise in Java and the Spring Framework ecosystem
Advanced knowledge of Spring Boot 3.x, Spring Security, and WebFlux
Regular use of AI coding assistants like GitHub Copilot
Strong experience with Apigee and reactive programming patterns
Proven ability to design and secure APIs using OAuth2, JWT, and API key management
Proficiency with AWS, Azure, or GCP cloud services
Hands-on experience integrating LLM APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic) and orchestrating prompts or agentic workflows
Familiarity with RAG, vector search, or embedding-based retrieval

Bonus Skills

Experience with real-time data processing and streaming architectures
Hosting model endpoints using platforms like AWS Bedrock
Familiarity with LangChain, CrewAI, or similar LLM orchestration frameworks
Graph API implementation
Experience with Kafka or similar message brokers

The good stuff…

Competitive remuneration and employee discounts. Make life easier (and more affordable) with $80 monthly credit and 25% off Optus products and unique shopping discounts with our retail partners.
Flexible working arrangements with opportunities to work three days in the office, two days remote or home.
Vibrant and collaborative office campus that includes cafes, convenience store, chill out zones, GP, post office, gym and on-site childcare centre.
Competitive leave policies, including additional 'Connected' days to focus on culture, family, health, community, or whatever's important to you.
We support growing families with inclusive, carer-neutral paid Parental Leave of up to 16 weeks.
Direct your own development and build future-ready skills with Optus U's industry-focused micro-credentials, developed with La Trobe and Macquarie Universities.
Build meaningful connections through employee-led networks and diversity initiatives including Culture Connect, Elevate Women, Disability Network and Express Yourself (LGBTQIA+).
Put your wellbeing first with free access to counselling and support services, 24/7 — in-person, by phone, SMS, or video.
Free Optus bus from Macquarie University Metro Station (every 6-8 minutes); morning and afternoon.

At Oracle Health and AI (OHAI), we're not just building the future of healthcare applications—we're redefining it. Our diverse team of visionaries and innovators is at the forefront of cutting-edge AI technology, particularly Generative AI, where creativity meets precision. As pioneers in this space, we've consistently delivered industry-leading AI solutions, notably for the Oracle Clinical Digital Assistant, solidifying our reputation as trusted leaders in the field.

Now, as we expand rapidly, we're channelling our expertise into transformative Generative AI solutions that promise to revolutionize healthcare for millions. Operating within a dynamic, agile environment, we enjoy strong backing from senior leadership and have a clear, impactful mission. Our close partnership with Oracle Cerner enables us to directly influence patient care on a massive scale, driving real change.

As our Senior AI Engineer, you'll be at the heart of this transformation, shaping the future of AI at OHAI. Your expertise in building applications leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) and Generative AI will be crucial in bringing our visionary solutions to life, delivering groundbreaking healthcare applications that will set new standards across the industry.

Career Level - IC3

As a world leader in cloud solutions, Oracle uses tomorrow’s technology to tackle today’s challenges. We’ve partnered with industry-leaders in almost every sector—and continue to thrive after 40+ years of change by operating with integrity. 

We know that true innovation starts when everyone is empowered to contribute. That’s why we’re committed to growing an inclusive workforce that promotes opportunities for all.

Oracle careers open the door to global opportunities where work-life balance flourishes. We offer competitive benefits based on parity and consistency and support our people with flexible medical, life insurance, and retirement options. We also encourage employees to give back to their communities through our volunteer programs.

We’re committed to including people with disabilities at all stages of the employment process. If you require accessibility assistance or accommodation for a disability at any point, let us know by emailing 

accommodation-request_mb@oracle.com or by calling +1 888 404 2494 in the United States.

Oracle is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability and protected veterans’ status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Oracle will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records pursuant to applicable law. 

 Responsibilities:

Collaborate with internal teams or external vendors to collect and curate high-quality data for training and testing AI models.
Rapidly develop AI-based prototypes and demos to showcase solutions and ideas to stakeholders, incorporating their feedback into future development iterations.
Define and implement sophisticated evaluation metrics to measure and analyze model performance.
Run experiments and optimize models through hyperparameter tuning to achieve peak performance.
Conduct quantitative and qualitative analysis, including error analysis and ablation studies, to enhance model development and data quality.
Prepare detailed reports with evidence-based insights to support strategic decision-making.
Work closely with team members to ensure successful and timely model delivery and service integration.
Develop innovative healthcare and enterprise services by leveraging the latest advancements in generative AI, machine learning, and deep learning.
Participate actively in project planning, review, and retrospective sessions.
Write production-grade code, advocate for best coding practices, and conduct peer reviews to maintain high engineering standards.

Qualifications and Experience:

Proven experience designing and deploying scalable AI models for production environments, with a successful track record of applying AI in real-world applications. Experience building applications using Large Language Models (LLMs) is a strong advantage.
Demonstrated hands-on experience in full-stack development of generative AI models, from data preparation to model deployment, ensuring end-to-end AI system functionality.
Practical experience with emerging LLM frameworks and plugins such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, VectorStores, Retrievers, LLM Cache, LLMOps (MLFlow), LMQL, and Guidance, showcasing your ability to stay at the forefront of AI technology.
Proven experience in designing data collection and annotation solutions, as well as systematic evaluation processes crucial for developing and maintaining high-quality production systems.
Strong collaboration skills with cross-functional teams, including data scientists, software engineers, and product managers, to integrate AI solutions into broader systems and deliver impactful results.
Demonstrated experience in optimizing, scaling, and monitoring AI systems in production environments, ensuring models meet performance, reliability, and scalability requirements.

Preferred Qualifications:

Knowledge of the healthcare domain and experience in delivering AI models specifically for healthcare applications are highly desirable.
Familiarity with the latest advancements in computer vision and multimodal modeling is a valuable plus.
Familiarity with UI/UX development is a plus, helping to bridge the gap between AI models and end-user applications, ensuring AI solutions are user-friendly and deliver excellent user experiences.

Education:

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, AI, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.

Oracle is committed to incorporating generative AI into our applications and workflows for business users. This role presents a unique opportunity to work on pioneering AI technologies and contribute to Oracle's Generative AI strategy. At Oracle, we value diversity and encourage continuous learning for career growth. Come join our team to make a significant difference!

Our Why

We’re seeking a self-motivated professional who takes pride in producing high-quality work, demonstrates exceptional attention to detail, and embraces a mindset of continuous improvement. What you’ll do

Lead the design and delivery of automation solutions that revolutionise workplace processes and streamline IT service delivery
Collaborate with internal and external customers to uncover opportunities for efficiency and innovation—including integration with AI models and large language models (LLMs).
Develop advanced scripts, integrations, and automation workflows using the latest cloud platforms and automation tools.
Mentor and inspire colleagues, sharing your expertise to elevate our Intelligent Workspace solutions.
Drive alignment across technical teams to ensure automation projects support our broader workplace strategy.
Champion best practices and provide technical guidance and training on automation tools and processes.

We’re agile and responsive to changing needs—your role will evolve as technology and customer requirements do.

What you’ll bring

Required Experience:

Proven experience designing and implementing process automation solutions within a workplace or IT environment.
Strong capabilities with automation tools and scripting languages (e.g., PowerShell, Python, RPA platforms).
Experience integrating systems and workflows within Microsoft 365 or comparable enterprise environments.
Ability to work collaboratively with technical and non-technical stakeholders to deliver automation projects.
Proven experience in driving continuous improvement initiatives, with a track record of identifying and implementing enhancements to workflows, systems, or processes. Demonstrates precision and thoroughness in execution, ensuring high-quality outcomes through strong attention to detail.

Desired Experience:

Familiarity with Modern Work concepts, including modern device management, digital collaboration tools, and end-user computing.
Experience with Azure infrastructure and services including Logic Apps, Log Analytics and Azure Key Vault.
Hands-on experience with Azure DevOps, including the design, implementation, and maintenance of CI/CD pipelines and code repositories, ensuring efficient, secure, and scalable software delivery practices.
Knowledge of ServiceNow, ITSM tools, or workflow automation platforms.
Industry certifications relevant to automation and/or modern workplace solutions.

Data Engineer - Commercial Risk Analytics

An exciting opportunity has become available for a passionate and innovative professional to join our dynamic Commercial Risk Analytics Team. In this role, you will be transforming data into actionable insights that drive business success, while ensuring the detailed integration of cutting-edge technology and strategic analytics.

This is a hybrid role with the flexibility to work both virtually and from our Aon offices.

Aon is in the business of better decisions

At Aon, we shape decisions for the better to protect and enrich the lives of people around the world.

As an organization, we are united through trust as one inclusive, diverse team, and we are passionate about helping our colleagues and clients succeed.

What the day will look like

Data Assets Design: Develop and enhance data assets tailored to business needs, supporting analytics and intelligence projects.
Automated Pipelines: Create and lead automated data ingestion pipelines using Databricks with AWS S3, and SSIS with Microsoft Azure.
Data Quality: Implement routines for data cleaning and standardization, using Python in Databricks notebooks for quality assurance.
SQL Development: Craft SQL scripts for data views, optimizing data flows to introduce new report dimensions and metrics.
Deployment & Monitoring: Deploy notebooks and scripts in production, configure cloud auto-scaling, and supervise performance. Integrate API solutions for GenAI module triggers.
Troubleshooting: Address data ingestion and processing issues, ensuring smooth report generation in PowerBI.
Collaboration: Work closely with data scientists, domain experts, and commercial risk leaders to build data infrastructure to support a broad variety of client risk analytics and business intelligence projects.
Technical Translation: Convert business requirements into technical specifications.

How this opportunity is different

As an Aon colleague, you will never be limited by your job title. Instead, you will learn and grow alongside some of the most versatile individuals in the business, who genuinely want you to be the best version of yourself.

We honestly believe that our culture is different, with authentic and inquisitive individuals who each bring something unique to our team.

Skills and experience that will lead to success

This role seeks for a forward-thinking Data Engineer to support our growing Commercial Risk Analytics team. Additionally, you will have the following:

5+ years of experience in data engineering, analytics, or business intelligence
Proficiency in SQL, Python, and cloud-based ETL tools like SSIS or Alteryx
Hands-on experience with Databricks (or similar platforms)
Knowledge of data architectures (data warehouses, lakehouse, and data mesh)
Skilled in Power BI for visualization and dashboard troubleshooting
Ability to document workflows, conduct testing, and ensure data quality
Experience integrating APIs and GenAI modules is a plus
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, or a related field (Master’s a plus)

Preferred

Databricks certification
Exposure to MLOps and Natural Language Processing (NLP)

 

How we support our colleagues

In addition to our comprehensive benefits package, we encourage a diverse workforce. Plus, our agile, inclusive environment allows you to manage your wellbeing and work/life balance, ensuring you can be your best self at Aon. Furthermore, all colleagues enjoy two “Global Wellbeing Days” each year, encouraging you to take time to focus on yourself. We offer a variety of working style solutions, but we also recognise that flexibility goes beyond just the place of work... and we are all for it. We call this Smart Working!

Our continuous learning culture inspires and equips you to learn, share and grow, helping you achieve your fullest potential. As a result, at Aon, you are more connected, more relevant, and more valued.
